WEBVTT

00:09.793 --> 00:11.103
[upbeat music]

00:11.172 --> 00:13.310
- Live from Presley's basement,

00:13.379 --> 00:16.103
it's open mic night!

00:16.172 --> 00:17.827
[both cheering]

00:17.896 --> 00:19.034
If I pick your name,

00:19.103 --> 00:20.310
that means you get five minutes

00:20.379 --> 00:22.241
to perform on this stage.

00:29.689 --> 00:32.413
- Okay, pick somebody.
- Hm.

00:34.068 --> 00:36.689
It's a receipt from when
we bought the fishbowl.

00:39.793 --> 00:42.344
Hm. "Prees-ly."

00:42.413 --> 00:44.172
Is there a "Prees-ly" anywhere?

00:44.241 --> 00:47.206
- You know it's me and that
I just have sloppy handwriting.

00:49.137 --> 00:50.965
- Hey, what are you gonna do
with that popcorn?

00:51.034 --> 00:55.000
- Quiet, this is my time.

00:55.068 --> 00:56.206
Now I bet you're wondering,

00:56.275 --> 00:59.172
what am I gonna do
with this popcorn?

00:59.241 --> 01:01.965
I am going to attempt

01:02.034 --> 01:04.241
to catch ten pieces of popcorn

01:04.310 --> 01:05.931
in my mouth...

01:06.000 --> 01:06.965
in a row.

01:07.034 --> 01:08.000
[both gasp]

01:08.068 --> 01:09.896
- It can't be done.

01:09.965 --> 01:11.379
- Please,

01:11.448 --> 01:13.827
I need complete and total
silence.

01:17.310 --> 01:18.724
[dinging]
- [yelps]

01:21.275 --> 01:22.793
Oh, come on!

01:24.620 --> 01:25.862
- Hey, we got a KidDING.

01:25.931 --> 01:26.931
- [gasps]

01:27.000 --> 01:28.896
The job is from Make-A-Mutt.

01:28.965 --> 01:30.931
- What's Make-A-Mutt?

01:31.000 --> 01:33.413
- What's Make-A-Mutt?

01:33.482 --> 01:36.172
What's Make-A-Mutt!?

01:36.241 --> 01:37.413
- Get ready, Munchy.

01:37.482 --> 01:40.413
Lex is about to go off
on a rant.

01:40.482 --> 01:42.344
- Make-A-Mutt is
a magical store

01:42.413 --> 01:44.000
where you design a stuffed dog

01:44.068 --> 01:45.241
and then a super cool machine,

01:45.310 --> 01:46.724
the Mutt-O-Matic, builds it.

01:46.793 --> 01:48.344
- Told you a rant was coming.

01:48.413 --> 01:51.551
She hasn't even gotten to
Nicholas the Ridiculous.

01:51.620 --> 01:52.896
- Who's Nicholas
the Ridiculous?

01:52.965 --> 01:55.241
- He's the amazing man
who runs the store

01:55.310 --> 01:56.379
with his sidekick, Waggles.

01:56.448 --> 01:58.482
- Who is Waggles?

01:58.551 --> 02:01.000
- You did this to yourself.

02:01.068 --> 02:03.793
- Waggles the dog
is the mascot of Make-A-Mutt.

02:03.862 --> 02:06.137
He was a stuffed animal
that Nicholas the Ridiculous

02:06.206 --> 02:07.344
brought to life.

02:07.413 --> 02:09.586
- You can't bring
a stuffed animal to life.

02:09.655 --> 02:12.413
[chuckling]
That's ridicul--

02:12.482 --> 02:14.793
Oh, now I get the name!

02:17.931 --> 02:20.620
- Presley, did you just eat
floor popcorn?

02:20.689 --> 02:25.000
- Quiet, this is my time.

02:25.068 --> 02:27.965
[upbeat music]

02:29.793 --> 02:31.275
[engine revving]

02:31.344 --> 02:34.241
[lively rock music]

02:34.310 --> 02:41.241
♪ ♪

02:41.310 --> 02:43.620
[motor shuts off]

02:43.689 --> 02:47.620
- Wow, you finally bought
a riding lawn mower.

02:47.689 --> 02:50.000
- Yeah, your mom
fought me hard,

02:50.068 --> 02:51.655
but I put my foot down.

02:51.724 --> 02:55.482
And waited for her to go
out of town to buy it.

02:55.551 --> 02:56.517
- Can I take it for a spin?

02:56.586 --> 02:59.827
- [chuckles]
Oh, Fisher.

02:59.896 --> 03:02.034
This is a serious
piece of machinery.

03:02.103 --> 03:03.724
It's for men with beards.

03:03.793 --> 03:06.413
Do you have a beard, son?

03:06.482 --> 03:10.344
- No, but I'm confident I can--
- That's right, no beard.

03:10.413 --> 03:11.965
Now, if you'll excuse me,

03:12.034 --> 03:15.000
I have to walk back
to get my car.

03:15.068 --> 03:18.000
- Wait, where's your car?

03:18.068 --> 03:19.655
- Couldn't wait to
ride this baby,

03:19.724 --> 03:21.310
so I drove it home
and left my car

03:21.379 --> 03:24.379
at the lawnmower shop.

03:24.448 --> 03:25.724
Also, I forgot to pay,

03:25.793 --> 03:28.482
so they definitely want me
to come back.

03:28.551 --> 03:30.379
Now, while I'm gone,

03:30.448 --> 03:31.896
hands off.

03:36.206 --> 03:38.034
- I can totally drive this.

03:45.241 --> 03:47.379
- Fisher, are you old enough
to drive that?

03:47.448 --> 03:49.034
- Of course I am.

03:49.103 --> 03:50.137
Watch.

03:50.206 --> 03:52.068
[engine revving]

03:52.137 --> 03:55.482
Ah, this kitten can purr.

03:55.551 --> 03:58.448
[lively rock music]

03:58.517 --> 04:04.413
♪ ♪

04:04.482 --> 04:06.827
Woo-hoo! This is awesome!

04:06.896 --> 04:08.793
- Okay, Fisher, slow down.

04:08.862 --> 04:10.172
- No way.

04:10.241 --> 04:11.448
[screaming]

04:11.517 --> 04:13.862
[crashing]

04:18.931 --> 04:21.689
Oh, no.

04:21.758 --> 04:24.862
- You are in so much trouble.

04:24.931 --> 04:27.482
- I know, and Dad just told me
not to drive it.

04:27.551 --> 04:28.551
What do I do?

04:28.620 --> 04:30.172
- You fix stuff all the time.

04:30.241 --> 04:31.551
Why don't you just fix it?

04:31.620 --> 04:33.896
- I fix electronics,
not garages.

04:35.413 --> 04:36.482
- Then my advice is for you to

04:36.551 --> 04:37.586
hop back on that lawn mower

04:37.655 --> 04:39.896
and ride it to Mexico.

04:39.965 --> 04:42.137
- So dead, I'm so dead,
I'm so dead!

04:42.206 --> 04:43.896
- You want this
taken care of quickly?

04:43.965 --> 04:45.620
- Yes.
- Call this number.

04:45.689 --> 04:48.172
[phones beep]

04:48.241 --> 04:49.517
- Who is this, a handyman?

04:49.586 --> 04:50.620
- Nope.

04:50.689 --> 04:52.620
Someone who fixes problems.

04:52.689 --> 04:54.379
They call her...

04:54.448 --> 04:57.482
[dramatically]
the Wombat.

04:57.551 --> 04:58.482
- The Wombat?

04:58.551 --> 04:59.965
- No.

05:00.034 --> 05:02.275
[dramatically]
The Wombat.

05:05.103 --> 05:08.034
[upbeat music]

05:08.103 --> 05:11.620
♪ ♪

05:11.689 --> 05:14.241
- I love this place so much.

05:14.310 --> 05:16.551
There's the Mutt-O-Matic
that makes the stuffed dogs,

05:16.620 --> 05:17.689
and there's the Mutt Maker

05:17.758 --> 05:19.103
where you customize
your friend.

05:19.172 --> 05:21.310
- Oh, look,
it's Waggles the dog.

05:21.379 --> 05:22.758
- Oh, but it's on a mannequin.

05:22.827 --> 05:23.896
There was always someone

05:23.965 --> 05:25.241
in the costume
when we were kids.

05:25.310 --> 05:26.655
- Aha!
So you admit that

05:26.724 --> 05:28.241
Waggles was never a real dog.

05:30.827 --> 05:32.758
- Okay, honey, hit the button.

05:32.827 --> 05:36.068
[triumphant horns]

05:36.137 --> 05:37.448
- That means
Nicholas the Ridiculous

05:37.517 --> 05:39.137
is coming.

05:39.206 --> 05:42.068
[goofy music playing]

05:43.379 --> 05:46.379
- Greetings, friend!

05:46.448 --> 05:48.896
I'm Nicholas the Ridiculous.

05:48.965 --> 05:50.620
Walk with me to the Mutt Maker.

05:50.689 --> 05:52.482
Remember, the sillier the walk,

05:52.551 --> 05:54.724
the more magical the creation.

06:00.413 --> 06:02.965
Let's make a mutt!

06:03.034 --> 06:05.551
- Watch, you can make your dog
any way you want.

06:05.620 --> 06:08.827
- [gasps]
I want to make my dog a cat.

06:08.896 --> 06:10.172
- That's not how it works.

06:12.896 --> 06:15.137
[Mutt-O-Matic powers up]

06:15.206 --> 06:17.931
- And now the Mutt-O-Matic
makes your new friend.

06:18.000 --> 06:21.103
[magical music playing]

06:21.172 --> 06:26.965
♪ ♪

06:27.034 --> 06:29.896
[trumpet fanfare]
[dog barks]

06:29.965 --> 06:32.379
- I love it!
- And she loves you!

06:32.448 --> 06:34.931
$49.99 plus tax.
Please pay here.

06:39.000 --> 06:40.793
Goodbye.

06:40.862 --> 06:43.068
- Um, excuse me,
Mr. Ridiculous.

06:43.137 --> 06:45.413
I don't know if you
remember me but--

06:45.482 --> 06:46.827
- Of course I remember you.

06:46.896 --> 06:49.206
You had your birthday here
three years in a row.

06:49.275 --> 06:51.413
One of your friends
always had too much licorice

06:51.482 --> 06:53.517
and threw up.

06:53.586 --> 06:55.793
- That was me.

06:55.862 --> 06:57.517
- Well, we're here for
the KidDING.

06:57.586 --> 06:58.896
- Yes, of course!

06:58.965 --> 07:00.827
Follow me to the back
where the mutts are made.

07:03.517 --> 07:06.413
- Oh, my gosh, we're gonna see
the inside of the Mutt-O-Matic!

07:09.413 --> 07:12.000
This is gonna be amazing.

07:15.448 --> 07:19.000
- Wow, so amazing.

07:19.068 --> 07:20.413
- What is this place?

07:20.482 --> 07:21.862
- Yeah, I thought we were gonna

07:21.931 --> 07:24.137
see the inside of
the magical machine.

07:24.206 --> 07:26.896
- You're looking at
the magical machine.

07:29.448 --> 07:30.448
- Wow.

07:30.517 --> 07:33.655
She looks so lifelike.

07:33.724 --> 07:35.068
- Marilyn isn't a machine.

07:35.137 --> 07:38.000
She's the person who puts
together the stuffed dogs.

07:38.068 --> 07:40.206
- No, but I thought
the Mutt-O-Matic made them.

07:40.275 --> 07:41.206
- I know.

07:41.275 --> 07:42.689
It's a little white lie we tell

07:42.758 --> 07:45.793
to help sell
the magic of the store.

07:45.862 --> 07:47.551
- I can't believe this.

07:47.620 --> 07:48.586
What else isn't real?

07:48.655 --> 07:49.724
- Yeah, I mean,

07:49.793 --> 07:51.758
are you even really ridiculous?

07:51.827 --> 07:53.413
- You tell me.

07:53.482 --> 07:55.965
Picnic table, picnic table,
picnic table!

07:57.448 --> 07:58.793
- Okay, you check out.

08:01.172 --> 08:03.793
- ♪ I got, you got me ♪
♪ We got this ♪

08:03.862 --> 08:06.172
♪ I like the odds when
we're side-by-side ♪

08:06.241 --> 08:08.103
♪ I like the sound of that ♪

08:08.172 --> 08:10.793
♪ Oh, we're taking off,
gonna do this right ♪

08:10.862 --> 08:12.344
♪ I like the sound of that ♪

08:12.413 --> 08:15.241
♪ And when things go up
in flames, we're on it ♪

08:15.310 --> 08:18.137
♪ 'Cause I got you, got me,
we got this ♪

08:24.413 --> 08:25.793
- I can't believe
this whole time

08:25.862 --> 08:28.310
there was a woman back here
making the stuffed dogs.

08:28.379 --> 08:31.000
My whole childhood is a lie.

08:31.068 --> 08:32.689
- In our defense,
we tried to make a machine

08:32.758 --> 08:33.965
that could make stuffed dogs,

08:34.034 --> 08:37.793
but it became self-aware
and tried to destroy us.

08:37.862 --> 08:39.793
- Been there.

08:39.862 --> 08:41.344
- Marilyn is retiring.

08:41.413 --> 08:43.103
I hired you kids
to take her place

08:43.172 --> 08:44.965
until we can find
a permanent replacement.

08:45.034 --> 08:47.000
[alarm buzzes]
- Oh!

08:47.068 --> 08:49.103
That light means
there's a customer.

08:49.172 --> 08:51.448
Two in one day?
We are killing it!

08:54.379 --> 08:56.379
- Let me show you
how this works.

08:56.448 --> 08:58.482
When a kid
customizes their doggy,

08:58.551 --> 08:59.965
it pops up on this screen

09:00.034 --> 09:01.137
and you hear a ding.

09:01.206 --> 09:03.310
[alert dings]

09:03.379 --> 09:05.655
the machine sends out
the stuffed dog body.

09:05.724 --> 09:08.896
Just attach the head,
arms, and legs

09:08.965 --> 09:10.344
like it looks on the screen.

09:10.413 --> 09:12.551
Put it all together,
blah, blah, blah.

09:12.620 --> 09:15.034
Magic, magic, magic,
and off it goes.

09:17.275 --> 09:21.344
[magical music playing]

09:21.413 --> 09:23.620
[trumpet fanfare]
[dog barks]

09:23.689 --> 09:24.931
- It's perfect!

09:25.000 --> 09:27.103
- And he will love you forever!

09:27.172 --> 09:30.103
That's $49.99 plus tax.
Please pay here.

09:31.517 --> 09:33.586
- Well good luck taking over.

09:33.655 --> 09:36.034
Nothing but palm trees,
fruity drinks,

09:36.103 --> 09:38.068
and luaus for me.

09:38.137 --> 09:39.965
I'm off to Rhode Island.

09:40.034 --> 09:42.137
Woo-hoo!

09:43.413 --> 09:44.586
- Guys,

09:44.655 --> 09:46.000
I don't know if
I feel good working here

09:46.068 --> 09:47.310
and lying to kids.

09:47.379 --> 09:48.862
- This place may have
lied to you,

09:48.931 --> 09:50.241
but it made you happy.

09:50.310 --> 09:51.655
Now it's your turn to lie

09:51.724 --> 09:52.931
and make other kids happy.

09:53.000 --> 09:55.379
It's the cycle of
lying and happiness.

10:00.586 --> 10:01.586
- Nice 'sault.

10:01.655 --> 10:03.379
- Thanks.

10:03.448 --> 10:05.137
- Did Marilyn show you
everything?

10:05.206 --> 10:06.896
- Yep, we're ready to
get to work.

10:06.965 --> 10:08.241
- Oh.
[chuckles]

10:08.310 --> 10:10.275
There probably won't be
any more work today.

10:10.344 --> 10:12.275
Kids just aren't interested
in stuffed animals

10:12.344 --> 10:13.862
like they used to be.

10:13.931 --> 10:15.137
- That is so sad.

10:15.206 --> 10:17.758
- Kids stink.

10:17.827 --> 10:20.620
- I'm not sure how much longer
I can keep this place going.

10:20.689 --> 10:22.862
- Hey, maybe we can help
get the word out.

10:22.931 --> 10:24.275
- Yeah, we can hit the streets

10:24.344 --> 10:26.172
and tell people
to come to the store.

10:26.241 --> 10:28.000
- Are you sure people
will pay attention to you?

10:28.068 --> 10:29.724
- Oh, I'm sure.
I can be quite loud.

10:29.793 --> 10:30.862
Watch.

10:30.931 --> 10:32.448
Mutts! Mutts! Mutts!

10:32.517 --> 10:35.310
Mutts! Mutts! Mutts!
- Okay, we get it.

10:37.068 --> 10:39.000
- Hey, I know how
to get their attention.

10:39.068 --> 10:40.137
- [gasps]
Yes!

10:40.206 --> 10:41.517
I'll put on
the Waggles costume.

10:41.586 --> 10:43.241
- Then we can make signs
for Make-A-Mutt

10:43.310 --> 10:44.482
and spin them around.

10:44.551 --> 10:46.379
- Let's go lie
to some children!

10:46.448 --> 10:47.931
all: Yeah!

10:48.000 --> 10:51.068
[upbeat music]

10:52.827 --> 10:55.206
- There.

10:55.275 --> 10:56.896
Maybe Dad won't notice.

10:56.965 --> 10:59.551
- You're not gonna fix this
problem with a houseplant.

11:01.655 --> 11:03.517
- Are you the Wombat?
- No.

11:03.586 --> 11:05.689
I'm...the Wombat.

11:08.137 --> 11:09.310
I solve problems.

11:09.379 --> 11:10.689
- Why are you wearing a tuxedo?

11:10.758 --> 11:12.931
- I'm not here to chit chat.

11:13.000 --> 11:15.551
Let's see your mess.

11:15.620 --> 11:17.827
Uh-huh.

11:17.896 --> 11:19.931
Uh-huh.

11:20.000 --> 11:22.206
Uh-huh!

11:22.275 --> 11:23.620
- My dad's gonna be back soon.

11:23.689 --> 11:25.862
If he sees that I crashed
his new lawn mower,

11:25.931 --> 11:27.344
he'll never forgive me.

11:27.413 --> 11:29.931
- If you do what I say,
when I say it,

11:30.000 --> 11:32.034
I'll get you out of this mess.

11:32.103 --> 11:34.344
Now, first thing I need
is some lemonade.

11:34.413 --> 11:36.793
Lots of lemons, lots of sugar.

11:36.862 --> 11:38.448
- I guess I could get you--
- I'll also need a blender,

11:38.517 --> 11:42.275
an inflatable palm tree,
and a bear trap.

11:42.344 --> 11:44.724
- How is that gonna help?
- The answers will come

11:44.793 --> 11:47.724
at the end of this journey.

11:47.793 --> 11:50.103
Still waiting on my lemonade.

11:50.172 --> 11:51.172
Go, go, go!

11:51.241 --> 11:53.068
- Right, right away, sir.

11:53.137 --> 11:54.551
I mean, ma'am.

11:54.620 --> 11:56.551
I mean, Wombat!

11:56.620 --> 11:58.655
[upbeat music]

11:58.724 --> 11:59.827
[car horn honking]

11:59.896 --> 12:01.655
[funky music]

12:01.724 --> 12:04.103
- Come to Make-A-Mutt!

12:04.172 --> 12:06.034
Tell 'em Waggles sent you!

12:06.103 --> 12:07.758
- I'm Waggles!

12:07.827 --> 12:11.379
♪ ♪

12:11.448 --> 12:13.862
- Attention, shoppers.

12:13.931 --> 12:16.379
- Looking for a place to strut?

12:16.448 --> 12:19.172
- Well, come on down
to Make-A-Mutt!

12:19.241 --> 12:24.413
♪ ♪

12:24.482 --> 12:28.172
- Now the whole town can
see our signs!

12:28.241 --> 12:31.000
- I'm a flying dog!

12:31.068 --> 12:32.448
- Hey, wait.

12:32.517 --> 12:34.586
Aren't you afraid of heights?

12:34.655 --> 12:35.758
- Oh, yeah.

12:35.827 --> 12:39.793
[screaming]

12:39.862 --> 12:42.344
- Oh, no, my sign!

12:42.413 --> 12:46.275
Look out below!

12:46.344 --> 12:47.862
- ♪ I'm stopping for
a milkshake ♪

12:47.931 --> 12:50.034
♪ On my way to the
lawn mower store ♪

12:50.103 --> 12:53.241
♪ Where I left my car
in the parking lot-- ♪

13:05.758 --> 13:07.241
[slurping]

13:07.310 --> 13:10.379
[upbeat music]

13:12.965 --> 13:15.379
- All right, I got
all the stuff you asked for.

13:15.448 --> 13:17.068
Now can we fix my garage?

13:17.137 --> 13:18.931
My dad will be here soon.

13:19.000 --> 13:20.793
- That's why I'm here.

13:20.862 --> 13:23.310
All I need now is
electrical tape, a whisk,

13:23.379 --> 13:25.172
and a rocking horse.

13:25.241 --> 13:28.068
- A "please" would be nice.

13:28.137 --> 13:29.379
- Listen, pal.

13:29.448 --> 13:30.827
Time is a factor.

13:30.896 --> 13:32.137
I think fast, I talk fast,

13:32.206 --> 13:33.413
and I need you to act fast

13:33.482 --> 13:35.965
if you want to
get out of this jam.

13:36.034 --> 13:37.172
- Fine.

13:37.241 --> 13:38.586
- I also drink fast.

13:38.655 --> 13:40.724
So get me some more lemonade.

13:42.379 --> 13:45.862
- [sighs]
- Go, go, go, go, go!

13:45.931 --> 13:48.758
[upbeat music]

13:48.827 --> 13:51.379
- And that's how
you get out of jury duty.

13:53.379 --> 13:55.931
- Nicholas the Ridiculous,
it worked.

13:56.000 --> 13:58.482
We got you a ton of customers.

13:58.551 --> 14:01.448
- And I got over
my fear of heights.

14:04.241 --> 14:05.551
- This is stupendous!

14:05.620 --> 14:06.586
It's time for the Mutt-O-Matic

14:06.655 --> 14:08.724
to make a dog for everyone!

14:08.793 --> 14:10.310
all: Yeah!

14:10.379 --> 14:12.310
- No, I mean get in the back
and make some stuffed dogs.

14:12.379 --> 14:14.034
- Oh, right.

14:14.103 --> 14:16.344
- All right, kids.
Who wants to see some juggling?

14:16.413 --> 14:18.206
- I do!
- Great.

14:18.275 --> 14:19.448
Follow-up question,
does anyone here

14:19.517 --> 14:21.689
know how to juggle?

14:23.862 --> 14:25.206
[alert dings]

14:25.275 --> 14:26.413
- Oh, that's cute.

14:26.482 --> 14:28.275
A dog with an orange head,
blue arms,

14:28.344 --> 14:29.931
and a green tail.

14:35.586 --> 14:37.137
- Oh, that wasn't so bad.

14:37.206 --> 14:38.310
[alert dings]

14:38.379 --> 14:40.275
- Oh, looks like
we got another order.

14:40.344 --> 14:41.965
[alert dings]
- Oh, looks like we got

14:42.034 --> 14:44.068
two new orders.
- On it.

14:44.137 --> 14:46.620
- Head, tail.
- Arm, arm.

14:46.689 --> 14:49.586
- Head, tail.
- Arm, arm.

14:49.655 --> 14:50.931
- Looks like
we found our rhythm.

14:51.000 --> 14:53.620
Easy peasy.

14:53.689 --> 14:54.862
[trumpet fanfare]
[dog barks]

14:54.931 --> 14:57.275
- Oh, isn't the
Mutt-O-Matic amazing?

14:57.344 --> 15:00.931
This is a perfect time to
order more mutts.

15:01.000 --> 15:03.000
- I want one.

15:05.793 --> 15:07.379
[alert dings]
- Yay, another order.

15:07.448 --> 15:09.000
[alert dings]
And another order.

15:09.068 --> 15:10.379
[alert dings]
Another?

15:10.448 --> 15:13.448
[alert dinging]
- Uh, that's a lot of mutts.

15:14.551 --> 15:20.793
[alert dinging]

15:20.862 --> 15:24.413
[alert dinging repeatedly]
- Oh, come on.

15:24.482 --> 15:26.068
- Blue.
- Green.

15:26.137 --> 15:27.206
Okay, yeah, you're right.

15:27.275 --> 15:28.517
- Moving fast.

15:28.586 --> 15:29.827
[alert dinging repeatedly]

15:29.896 --> 15:31.068
- Green, pink.

15:31.137 --> 15:32.896
Come on.

15:32.965 --> 15:34.241
Kay.
- Is this right?

15:34.310 --> 15:36.034
Okay.

15:36.103 --> 15:38.965
Things are moving so fast.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, okay!

15:39.034 --> 15:41.137
- No, no. No tail!

15:41.206 --> 15:44.000
[trumpet fanfare]
[dogs barking]

15:44.068 --> 15:47.862
[alert dinging repeatedly]
[both screaming]

15:47.931 --> 15:49.344
- Okay, come on!

15:49.413 --> 15:51.275
- [stammering]

15:51.344 --> 15:53.758
[alert dinging repeatedly]
- [yelps]

15:53.827 --> 15:57.965
Okay, this isn't easy or peasy!
- [screams]

15:58.034 --> 16:00.689
[upbeat music]

16:03.862 --> 16:06.620
- Work faster, Lex!

16:06.689 --> 16:08.379
[alert dinging repeatedly]

16:08.448 --> 16:09.827
So many!

16:09.896 --> 16:12.655
- Too many dogs
coming too fast!

16:12.724 --> 16:14.206
- Now I see why Marilyn retired

16:14.275 --> 16:16.896
to the tropical beaches
of Rhode Island!

16:16.965 --> 16:20.241
[alert dinging]
Can you hand me a blue head?

16:24.068 --> 16:26.793
- Okay, hand me a purple tail,

16:26.862 --> 16:28.965
- I don't have any
purple tails!

16:29.034 --> 16:33.241
[alert dinging repeatedly]
Are you serious right now?

16:33.310 --> 16:35.000
- Okay, it's got to
slow down soon, right?

16:35.068 --> 16:36.793
There weren't that many kids
out there.

16:38.344 --> 16:39.448
- Nicholas, check it out.

16:39.517 --> 16:40.931
A birthday party.

16:41.000 --> 16:42.827
We should crank the
Mutt-O-Matic up to go faster.

16:42.896 --> 16:45.689
- Great idea, Waggles!

16:48.586 --> 16:51.655
[alert dinging repeatedly]

16:51.724 --> 16:53.000
- Kay, Presley, hurry up.

16:55.793 --> 16:57.931
- What is going on out there?

17:00.000 --> 17:03.793
[trumpet fanfare]
[dogs barking]

17:03.862 --> 17:05.620
- Okay, I know this is hard,

17:05.689 --> 17:07.793
but we have to make sure
each dog is perfect

17:07.862 --> 17:09.310
for the kids out there
in the store.

17:09.379 --> 17:12.931
[alert dinging]

17:13.000 --> 17:14.137
- [yelps]

17:14.206 --> 17:20.137
[alert dinging]

17:20.206 --> 17:21.827
- This isn't the stuffed animal
I ordered.

17:21.896 --> 17:25.413
It has an arm for a tail.

17:25.482 --> 17:26.827
- Mine is wrong, too.

17:26.896 --> 17:29.448
It's all tails.

17:29.517 --> 17:30.793
- Mine doesn't have a head.

17:30.862 --> 17:34.448
- Mine has a head
coming out of its butt.

17:34.517 --> 17:36.241
- Fix it!
- This isn't fair.

17:36.310 --> 17:38.931
all: Fix it!

17:39.000 --> 17:41.034
[alert dinging repeatedly]

17:45.206 --> 17:46.896
- Gosh.

17:47.724 --> 17:49.620
- Everyone, I assure you

17:49.689 --> 17:52.482
the Mutt-O-Matic
is working just fine.

17:52.551 --> 17:54.034
- Okay, we gotta catch up!

17:54.103 --> 17:56.482
We can't send out
anymore wrong dogs.

17:56.551 --> 17:58.068
- That dog has two heads!

17:58.137 --> 17:59.862
- No!

18:02.931 --> 18:05.310
- Lex, I have your shoes.
I'll keep them safe!

18:13.586 --> 18:15.448
- I'm your new doggy!

18:15.517 --> 18:17.620
- [screaming]

18:17.689 --> 18:20.620
[upbeat music]

18:20.689 --> 18:23.758
♪ ♪

18:23.827 --> 18:25.896
- Hurry it up, Fisher.

18:30.206 --> 18:31.034
- Here.

18:31.103 --> 18:32.793
Here's your stupid alpaca.

18:35.034 --> 18:37.931
- Can you believe
this guy called you stupid?

18:38.000 --> 18:39.517
[as alpaca]
I know, Wombat.

18:39.586 --> 18:42.241
But at least I know how to
drive a lawn mower.

18:44.344 --> 18:46.620
- You're supposed to be
helping me fix my garage.

18:46.689 --> 18:47.758
Instead you have me
running around,

18:47.827 --> 18:48.793
getting random things.

18:48.862 --> 18:49.862
It would have just been easier

18:49.931 --> 18:51.413
to tell my dad the truth.

18:51.482 --> 18:55.068
- [claps slowly]

18:55.137 --> 18:57.206
And now you've reached
the end of your journey.

18:59.655 --> 19:01.724
- What happened to my garage?

19:03.000 --> 19:04.965
And why is there an alpaca
in the driveway?

19:06.517 --> 19:07.758
- I messed up, Dad.

19:07.827 --> 19:09.103
I drove your mower
into the garage

19:09.172 --> 19:11.172
and I didn't know
how to tell you.

19:11.241 --> 19:14.862
- Fish, you know you can
talk to me about anything.

19:14.931 --> 19:16.620
Even when you make mistakes.

19:16.689 --> 19:17.689
- I know.

19:17.758 --> 19:19.344
I should have been honest.

19:19.413 --> 19:20.758
- Boom!

19:20.827 --> 19:21.965
Lesson learned.

19:22.034 --> 19:23.724
My work here is done.

19:23.793 --> 19:25.551
You can keep all this stuff.

19:25.620 --> 19:27.689
Except this.

19:27.758 --> 19:29.000
It's coming with me.

19:31.862 --> 19:33.586
- So that's it?
I'm off the hook?

19:33.655 --> 19:35.758
- [chuckles]
Oh, no.

19:35.827 --> 19:38.655
You are going to fix this
garage door.

19:38.724 --> 19:40.137
And when you're done,

19:40.206 --> 19:41.896
I'm gonna give you some
riding lawn mower lessons.

19:41.965 --> 19:42.896
- Sounds good.

19:42.965 --> 19:44.275
- But first...

19:44.344 --> 19:46.137
I'm going to need
some lemonade.

19:46.206 --> 19:47.793
Go, go, go!

19:50.034 --> 19:51.344
I know, I know,

19:51.413 --> 19:53.103
I should be more firm
with Fisher,

19:53.172 --> 19:56.275
but it's hard
to stay mad at him.

19:56.344 --> 19:59.551
You have any kids?

19:59.620 --> 20:02.758
[upbeat music]

20:03.965 --> 20:05.827
- Is this really magical?

20:05.896 --> 20:07.862
Because it looks like that girl

20:07.931 --> 20:10.620
was working in that machine.

20:10.689 --> 20:12.034
- What?

20:12.103 --> 20:15.482
No, there is no one
working in the machine.

20:15.551 --> 20:17.793
That is crazy.

20:17.862 --> 20:20.517
- [muffled]
Lex, Lex!

20:20.586 --> 20:23.068
[grunting]

20:25.689 --> 20:27.724
I have your shoes.

20:29.000 --> 20:32.551
Hey, why is everyone
staring at us?

20:32.620 --> 20:34.137
- We want a refund.

20:34.206 --> 20:36.896
all: Refund, refund, refund!

20:36.965 --> 20:38.172
- Okay, everyone.

20:38.241 --> 20:40.620
May I please
have your attention.

20:40.689 --> 20:42.034
Okay, I know that
you're upset that

20:42.103 --> 20:44.758
the Mutt-O-Matic isn't
magical like you thought.

20:44.827 --> 20:46.551
But the real magic
comes from the joy

20:46.620 --> 20:49.068
of making a friend that
will be with you guys forever.

20:50.206 --> 20:51.827
- I want a dog with a head.

20:51.896 --> 20:53.413
[children agreeing]

20:54.896 --> 20:57.793
[magical music playing]

20:57.862 --> 21:03.793
♪ ♪

21:03.862 --> 21:05.655
- Wait, how is
the machine running?

21:05.724 --> 21:07.482
No one's back there.

21:07.551 --> 21:09.034
- Maybe it is magical.

21:09.103 --> 21:11.862
[magical music stirs]

21:11.931 --> 21:13.034
[dog barks]

21:14.965 --> 21:17.068
- This is the dog I wanted!

21:17.137 --> 21:19.827
- It's a Make-A-Mutt miracle!

21:19.896 --> 21:22.344
[all cheering]

21:22.413 --> 21:25.172
That's $49.99.
Please pay over there.

21:27.172 --> 21:28.448
- I gotta see this.

21:34.793 --> 21:36.068
- Marilyn?

21:36.137 --> 21:38.000
I thought you retired to
Rhode Island.

21:38.068 --> 21:42.034
- Turns out it was
more road than island.

21:42.103 --> 21:43.724
- Well, thanks for
bringing all the magic

21:43.793 --> 21:44.931
back to the store.

21:45.000 --> 21:46.827
- You've made
a lot of kids happy.

21:46.896 --> 21:49.896
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Warms my heart.

21:49.965 --> 21:52.586
[upbeat music]

21:53.620 --> 21:56.137
- Thank you for getting
Marilyn to come back, Wombat.

21:57.724 --> 21:58.896
- It's my thing, Nicholas.

21:58.965 --> 22:00.862
I fix problems.

22:00.931 --> 22:01.931
I'm taking this dog.

22:02.000 --> 22:02.965
I like it.

22:03.034 --> 22:05.931
It has a head on its butt.

22:06.000 --> 22:09.103
[upbeat music]
